  "prompt": "How do you put on fake eyelashes without glue?",
  "response": "Applying fake eyelashes without glue can be a bit tricky, but there are a few alternative methods you can try. Here are some options:\n\n### 1. **Magnetic Eyelashes:**\n   - **Magnetic Liner:** Use a magnetic eyeliner as the adhesive. Apply the liner along your lash line as you would with regular eyeliner. Once it dries, the magnetic lashes will cling to the liner.\n   - **Magnetic Lash Bands:** Some magnetic lashes come with two lash strips that sandwich your natural lashes. Place one strip on top of your natural lashes and the other underneath, and they will magnetically attach to each other.\n\n### 2. **Lash Adhesive Strips:**\n   - **Pre-Adhesive Strips:** Some fake lashes come with pre-applied adhesive strips. These lashes can be pressed directly onto your lash line without the need for additional glue. Just make sure to press them firmly in place for a few seconds.\n\n### 3. **Eyelash Tapes:**\n   - **Double-Sided Eyelash Tape:** You can use special double-sided eyelash tape designed for this purpose. Cut a small piece of the tape to fit the lash band, apply it to the band, and then press the lashes onto your lash line.\n\n### 4. **DIY Methods:**\n   - **Vaseline or Lip Balm:** While not as effective as glue, a tiny amount of Vaseline or lip balm can sometimes help adhere the lashes. Be cautious with this method, as it may not hold as well and could cause the lashes to slip.\n   - **Clear Eyebrow Gel:** A clear eyebrow gel can be applied to the lash band to help it stick to your natural lashes. This method is more suitable for subtle lash extensions rather than full strips.\n\n### Tips for Application:\n- **Trim the Lashes:** Always trim the lashes to fit your eye shape before applying.\n- **Positioning:** Use tweezers or a lash applicator to help position the lashes correctly.\n- **Press and Hold:** Once the lashes are in place, press and hold them for a few seconds to ensure they adhere well.\n\nWhile these methods can work, they may not provide the same level of hold and longevity as traditional lash glue. Always test the method you choose to ensure it\u2019s comfortable and effective for your needs.",
